<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Well for years I used Ubuntu and macOS. Both of these are great, I still like Ubuntu but I started to feel its limits. It&#39;s too much userfriendly, which is not necessary a bad thing. My wife loves it. But for me it wasn&#39;t enough. Few weeks ago I switched from macOS to Ubuntu because of my new job. And now I switched to Fedora. I like the approach and I can say m&#39;lady. Cheers guys hope you are happy with whenever you are using! </p> <p><a href="https://preview.redd.it/xnx7fihe0nd91.png?width=1032&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=859bedcae8aec9bb3558a88a84647b4b8df71ce3">https://preview.redd.it/xnx7fihe0nd91.png?width=1032&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=859bedcae8aec9bb3558a88a84647b4b8df71ce3</a></p> <p><a href="https://preview.redd.it/6rluqgie0nd91.png?width=1102&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=f286e0a62be8faf167f8f85c0b118722ecc5b9ee">https://preview.redd.it/6rluqgie0nd91.png?width=1102&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=f286e0a62be8faf167f8f85c0b118722ecc5b9ee</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/paulix96"> /u/paulix96 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w7eoj3/first_time_using_something_else_than_ubuntu_as/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w7eoj3/first_time_using_something_else_than_ubuntu_as/">[comments]</a></span>